1. Extract Data
To begin, you need to read data from the provided CSV files (order_origin_A.csv and order_origin_B.csv).

Write a PySpark function to read data from the provided files.
python
Copy code
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.functions import col, expr, concat, lit

def read_data(file_path):
    spark = SparkSession.builder \
        .appName("Sales Data Processing") \
        .getOrCreate()
    
    return spark.read.csv(file_path, header=True, inferSchema=True)

# Load data from both regions
df_A = read_data('order_origin_A.csv')
df_B = read_data('order_origin_B.csv')
